@NODE "What" "What is this shit?"
@TOC "MAIN"

                   What the bloody hell is Sysdudesend ?
                 -======================================-

You might know the problem... Annoying users who want files that aren't online
on the board. It happens all the time; Starting DOpus, searching through your
HD (and it is a mess, right?), packing with LHA/LZX, finding the right dir to
put your file in so the user can finally download the shitty thing.

This is the solution:

Buy yarself a Magnum .44 and blow your head clean off... You are a lamer,
the lowest lowlife scum in the world. The world is far better of without you.
(Aah.. I can still hear my teacher English saying that.. 8)

No, just kidding (in case you might haven't figured that out by now).

@{b}BK Sysdude Send @{ub}(short for Bad Karma Sysdude Send, if case you haven't
figured that out by now) is a file sender (in case you haven't figured
that out yet) with some really nice options (in case you haven't figured
that out yet) and a real sexy look (you will not figure this one
out), to give users files they want but you don't have online!

Right Right, I know you now are thinking 'Fuck you mate, all the bloody work
to install some fucking crappy amos-doors' but believe me, this one is worth
it! (And it ISN'T amos!)

Just read on to find out why...

 @{" Distribution " LINK "Distri"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Distri" "How should I spread this thing ?"
@TOC "MAIN"

                                 Distribution
                               -==============-

Okay, looks like this is going to be the only serious part in this doc :).

Well, I enjoyed writing this door, but as you might know, there's ALOT of 
work coding such things and I don't want my work to be worthless. That's
why I have decided to make Sysdudesend MAILWARE.

That's right, you still don't have to pay shit for using this program!
Just don't be lazy and let me know you are USING it! Just send me an
e-mail or a letter or I don't know what. (Letters can be sent to the
POBox mentioned in the @{" Bad Karma " LINK "BK"} part.

Okay, look at it this way: the more e-mail I get (don't touch that
massmail button, John) , the more encouraged I get for coding more
doors! So if you'd like to see some more BK doors coming from me,
then WRITE. Press that 'WRITE EMAIL MESSAGE' button NOW!

Well, what to write: Just say 'Hi I use it', or if you have any
suggestions/bug reports -duh-/presents/17-year old sisters
then include them in the mail ;)

Okay, thanks in advance to all e-mailers.

Messages/Letters received so far:
