@NODE "Why" "Why should I use this shit"
@TOC "MAIN"

                 Why the bloody hell should I use this one ?
                -===========================================-

Well, I haven't got a clue.

 @{" Features " LINK "Features"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Features" "Features of this shit"
@TOC "MAIN"

                 What the bloody hell is this babe capable of?
                -============================================-

Aha! All the nice thingies this door can do!

 *   AmiExpress v3.xx+ AND SigmaExpress compatible! [SELECTABLE]
 *   Password & Sysop-only protection               [SELECTABLE]
 *   Multiple File sending
 *   Multi Dir sending!
 *   Files-to-send overview                         [SELECTABLE]
 *   LZX & LHA packing of files
     (With user-definable archive names & default packerpath)
 *   Online help at every point!
 *   Allows sending from RAM:
     (Unlike some others who try to send from Ram Disk: !!)
 *   Extra security built in!

Yes! And what do you need to experience all these lovely things?

 * An Amiga
 * A Modem
 * A BBS-Program that ends on -express
 * A Kickstart 2.0 (do you know a nostalgic sysop running Kick 1.3??)
 * The ReqTools library (included in this archive)
 * The AEDoor.library   (also included, ain't I a nice guy 8)

The ReqTools library is copyright by Nico François, but hey, who gives a
fuck anyway, since Nico ditched his a4000 ?!?!

  @{" How the bloody 'ell do I install this ??? " LINK "How"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "How" "How should I use this shit"
@TOC "MAIN"

                   How the bloody hell should I use this ?
                  -=======================================-

Well, it's very simple:
First install it all. You can do it the easy way (Automatic) or the hard
way. (If you want to be the local pain in the ass).

@{b}Automatic Installation
-----------------------@{ub}

Really simple. Doubleclick the INSTALL_SYSDUDESEND icon & enjoy the computer
doing all the hard work!

@{b}Manual Installation
--------------------@{ub}

 @{"  Ami Express  " LINK "AXpress"}
 @{" Sigma Express " LINK "SXpress"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "AXpress" "Installation on Ami Express"
@TOC "MAIN"

                   Installation on a AmiExpress system
                  -===================================-

This one is real simple too (actually)! Just do this:

 * Look in the archive... There should be a drawer called COMMANDS in there.
   Go into it. There is a subdrawer called BBSCMD and also enter that one.
   Now copy the SS.info to you own BBS:Commands/BBSCmd drawer, adjust the
   accesslevel (tooltype ACCESS=) and go!

 * Copy the BK drawer from the DOORS drawer in the archive to your own DOORS:

 * Adjust the configuration file using the @{"tooltypes" LINK "TT"}

@{b}!*! NOTE !*!  YOU CANNOT PLACE THE DRAWER SOMEWHERE ELSE. THE DOOR IS HARDCODED
              TO READ ALL FILES FROM THE DOORS:BK/Sysdudesend/ DIR!! @{ub}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "SXpress" "Installation on Sigma Express"
@TOC "MAIN"

                  Installation on a SigmaExpress system
                 -=====================================-

This one is real simple too! Just do this:

 * Go to your BBS:COMMANDS drawer and locate the bbs.cmd file. Load it into an
   editor and add the following line:

       *SS       XM100DOORS:BK/SysdudeSend/SS.xim
       | |       |  | `=> Filename
       | |       |  `-==> Access level required to run the door
       | |       `-=====> XM type of door (executable)
       | `-=============> BBS command to start the door
       `-===============> Command works on ALL nodes

 * Copy the BK drawer from the DOORS drawer in the archive to your own DOORS:

 * Adjust the configuration file using the @{"tooltypes" LINK "TT"}

@{b}!*! NOTE !*!  YOU CANNOT PLACE THE DRAWER SOMEWHERE ELSE. THE DOOR IS HARDCODED
              TO READ ALL FILES FROM THE DOORS:BK/Sysdudesend/ DIR!! @{ub}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "TT" "Tooltypes for the installation procedure"
@TOC "MAIN"

A list of all tooltypes and their explanation:

@{b}PSW@{ub}            Here you can specify what password has to be used to start
               the door. If not defined, the default password, 666 , will be
               used.

@{b}REQUESTER@{ub}      This is the alternative to the password routines.
               If this tooltype is set, the password routine will be skipped,
               and a visual protection will be ran. A requester will open;
               This requester has to get closed within 4-5 seconds, or else
               the door will quit. (This will prevent users from starting
               the door and having the board hang the whole day!)
               I prefer this method, because it is faster, and safer!
               (Passwords are easily hacked, this will force the sysop to
               be present!)

@{b}DISPLAYFILES@{ub}   If this tooltype is set, Sysdudesend will first display
               a list of the files that are about to get transmitted.
               This will slowdown a bit, but will prevent you from
               sending wrong files (cardlists etc 8)..

@{b}PACKERPATH@{ub}     Here you can specify whether you want to use a default
               packerpath or not. If you don't specify a path, the files
               will be packed into the currentdir. (This usually is
               DH0: or DH0:WBStartup). If you want the files to be packed
               somewhere else, this is the place to specify it. You can
               enter pathnames here like RAM: or DH1:Pack/ or whatsoever.
               When using subdirs, don't forget the ending / !
@{b}EXTRACONFIRM@{ub}   This tooltype has been added for the doubtfull people
               out there. It gives you the chance to ABORT before sending.
               @{i}Note: This tooltype is only valid when DISPLAYFILES is selected.
                     You can't abort the sending of packed archives@{ui}.

 @{" Usage " LINK "Usage"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Usage" "Usage for this door"
@TOC "MAIN"

                           Usage of Sysdudesend
                          -====================-

How to use it:
(Note: @{b}bold@{ub} text equals the door output at the explained stage)

On the menu prompt, you have to type SS to start the door
(unless you renamed it). Depending on how you configured the door,
you will be prompted with a requester, begging to be closed, or
you will have to enter the password you specified in the tooltypes.

@{bg highlight} BaD KaRMa @{bg text}@{fg highlight} Sysdude Send V1.53 @{bg highlight}@{fg text} By [-cR!SP-] in 1996 @{bg background}

The door will then prompt you with a filerequester, in which you can
select the files you want to send. Press OK to continue.

Now AGAIN you will be prompted by another filerequester. This is the cewl
thingy about the door. If you want to send MORE files (thus from other
directories) then you can select them here (and you can keep on selecting!)
If you have selected all the files, just press OK (WITHOUT SELECTING A FILE!)

@{b}Pack file? (y/N/?/a)@{ub}

The door will then ask you if you want to pack the files.
If you are sending an already packed file, select (n)o here.
(Help is available here by pressing ? or H. You can abort with a/A)
If you press (n)o and you have defined the EXTRACONFIRM tooltype,
then you will be prompted whether you REALLY want to send the files
or not. If you haven't defined the EXTRACONFIRM tooltype, the
sending will automatically start.

Now, back to the packerthingy:
If you press (Y)es , you get the choise between LHA, LZX and ZIP.

@{b}Please select the packer you want to use:
 (1) LHA/LZH
 (2) LZX
 (3) ZIP

Choose: (1-3/?/a)@{ub}

Select the packer you want by pressing the number in front of it.
(Help is available here by pressing ? or H and aborting is done with a/A)

@{b}Please enter destination archivename : @{ub}

Then, the door will ask you the archivename for the packer. Here you can enter
a name (with or without path/with or without archivetype extension)
(eg: RAM:PACKED.LZX   or DH1:PACKED).
If you haven't specified a default dir, the file will be packed into the
currentdir (read @{"tooltypes" LINK "TT"} for more info). If you have
specified a default dir & the dir you entered here DIFFERS from the
defaultdir, you will be promped with the question if you want to
use the selected dir or the default dir.

@{b}You selected a packing dir different from the defaultdir you specified.
You selected       : @{ub}<selected dirname>
@{b}The default dir is : @{ub}<default dirname>
@{b}Do you wish to use the default dir ? (Y/n)@{ub}

Press Y here to use the default dir or N to use the selected dir

@{b}Please wait while packing files...@{ub}

The files will be packed and send to the user using ZModem.

Voila, the door quits with a 'ZMODEM DOWNLOAD SUCCESSFULL' message!

 @{" Read me too!" LINK "LW"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "BUGS" "Know bugs"
@TOC "MAIN"

                                Known Bugs
                               -==========-

 * When using /X, the sending won't work when the user has put his
   setting to HYDRA. This is an internal /X bug!
   (For /X users, i can only advice to use S!X, as it doesn't have this
    bug!).

   When I get some updates of the /X (or S!X) doordocs that tell me how
   to use external protocols, i will update BK-Sysdudesend to work with them!

@ENDNODE

@NODE "History" "The making of .... "
@TOC "MAIN"

                                 History
                               -=========-

@{b}  v1.53       18.08.96          FOURTH PUBLIC RELEASE
                                Some minor bugfixes here. Also added a new tooltype
                                called EXTRACONFIRM.
                                Also new is a memory allocated block for storing the
                                filenames.@{ub}

@{b}  v1.52        03.06.96         THIRD PUBLIC RELEASE
                                Added new tooltype: PACKERPATH@{ub}

  v1.51        02.06.96         Fixed a bug: BK-SS wouldn't take the default value when RETURN was
                                pressed on prompts
  v1.50        24.04.96         Fixed another ZIP-bug. BK-SS would forget to delete the file after sending
                                Added 'Abort' option to menus
                                Added online help

  v1.13        02.04.96         SECOND PUBLIC RELEASE
                                Fixed the extension buggy code: Now ANY extension may be entered.
                                BK-SS will replace it by the filetypes extension.
                                Fixed the ZIP-packing bug. Now it won't hang the node anymore.
                                Added 'Ram Disk:' sending (failed because of space in 'Ram Disk:')

  v1.11        23.03.96         Added sysop-definable filenames option
  v1.1         20.03.96         Fixing the layout (changed some colors)
                                Smucking up the hotkey-code
                                Added ZIP packing

  v1.0         29.01.96         FIRST PUBLIC RELEASE

  v0.93ß       15.01.96         INTERNAL RELEASE
  v0.1ß        29.07.95         INTERNAL RELEASE

